                            <comment id="13624734" author="hshreedharan" created="Sun, 7 Apr 2013 05:48:27 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Most of the code is generated code. The code change itself is minimal.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13624735" author="hshreedharan" created="Sun, 7 Apr 2013 05:49:12 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The relevant changes are in the top level pom and ThriftSource.java - all other changes are just changes in generated code.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13625045" author="hshreedharan" created="Sun, 7 Apr 2013 23:11:36 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Seems like in hbase-94 we can use thrift-0.8+. The TThreadSelectorServer gives far better perf (available only in thrift-0.8), so we should use that in the Hadoop-2 profile. It will be a bit &quot;dirty&quot;, since we need to use reflection, but I think it is worth it. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13625139" author="mpercy" created="Mon, 8 Apr 2013 05:04:05 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1, lgtm, good to reduce the hbase version dep for compat. Unit tests pass so I&apos;m committing this.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13625140" author="mpercy" created="Mon, 8 Apr 2013 05:05:49 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Pushed to trunk &amp;amp; flume-1.4 branches. Thanks for the patch Hari!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
